Johnson Leads All Stars To Victory 
Magic Johnson scored 30 points Wednesday night as his American All
Stars to a 106-99 victory over the Australian national team in an
exhibition basketball match.
The win was the second straight for the All Stars, who defeated
Australia 113-98 in Adelaide on Tuesday night.
Former Detroit Piston Mark Aguirre hit 22 points for the All Stars,
while Brett Maher led Australia with 19.
The game was the second in the five-match series between Johnson's team
-- unbeaten in 36 exhibition matches -- and the Australians.
Further games will be played in Melbourne, Sydney and Perth.
